Title: Security update for maven, maven-resolver, sbt, xmvn

Notes.Text: Security update for maven, maven-resolver, sbt, xmvn
Notes.Title: Topic

Notes.Text:
This update for maven, maven-resolver, sbt, xmvn fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2023-46122: Fixed an arbitrary file write when extracting a
  crafted zip file with sbt (bsc#1216529).
- Upgraded maven to version 3.9.4
- Upgraded maven-resolver to version 1.9.15.

Vulnerabilities.Description: sbt is a build tool for Scala, Java, and others. Given a specially crafted zip or JAR file, `IO.unzip` allows writing of arbitrary file. This would have potential to overwrite `/root/.ssh/authorized_keys`. Within sbt's main code, `IO.unzip` is used in `pullRemoteCache` task and `Resolvers.remote`; however many projects use `IO.unzip(...)` directly to implement custom tasks. This vulnerability has been patched in version 1.9.7.
